The Herald Herald Reporter
President Mnangagwa has presided over the joint burial of the late Manicaland Provincial Affairs and Devolution Minister Dr Ellen Gwaradzimba and the late Zanu PF Central Committee member Cde Morton Dizzy Paul Malianga at the National Heroes’ Acre in Harare. <img class="wp-image-525721 size-full" src="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/01/Heroes-2.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="453" srcset="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/01/Heroes-2.jpg 680w, https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/01/Heroes-2-360x240.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> National Hero Malianga and National Heroine Gwaradzimba were laid to rest at The National Heroes Acre on Thursday afternoon The double burial was the third ever following the double burials of national heroines Cde Victoria Chitepo and Vivian Mwashita in 2016 and Cde George Rutanhire and Cde Maud Muzenda in 2017. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-525720 size-full" src="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/01/heroes-3.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="453" srcset="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/01/heroes-3.jpg 680w, https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/01/heroes-3-360x240.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" />The interments followed strict Covid-19 control measures, with only a few people at the shrine. President Mnangagwa described the late freedom fighters as selfless in their pursuit for liberation. <img class="wp-image-525722 size-full" src="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/01/Heroes-1.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="411" srcset="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/01/Heroes-1.jpg 680w, https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/01/Heroes-1-360x218.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Scenes from the National Heroes Acre during the double burial of Cdes Malianga and Gwaradzimba. He implored the nation to work hard to complete the final nail of liberation-economic liberty. “Until now, this is the Zimbabwe that we all want and indeed the Zimbabwe we must all work hard to realise,” said President Mnangagwa.